cat > ~/ocp-ai-config/oauth/README.md << 'EOF'
# OAuth LDAP Configuration

The OAuth config references two resources in the `openshift-config` namespace
that are NOT managed by ArgoCD or ESO (intentionally — to avoid locking out
the cluster if ESO has issues).

## Recreating after cluster rebuild

The bind password and CA cert are backed up in Vault:
```bash
# Recreate the bind password secret
vault kv get -field=bindPassword kv/ldap-group-sync/bind-password > /tmp/ldap-bind-password
oc create secret generic ldap-bind-password-8gk5w \
  --from-file=bindPassword=/tmp/ldap-bind-password \
  -n openshift-config

# Recreate the CA configmap
vault kv get -field=ca.crt kv/ldap-group-sync/ldap-ca > /tmp/ldap-ca.crt
oc create configmap ldap-ca-m4hvn \
  --from-file=ca.crt=/tmp/ldap-ca.crt \
  -n openshift-config
```

After creating these, ArgoCD will sync the OAuth config and LDAP login will work.
EOF



